# Adding a New Tenant

## Required Steps

1. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/config.ts` with `TenantConfig` (id, name, domains, theme, adapter)
2. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/blocks/index.ts` — register blocks via `registerTenantBlocks("{tenant-id}", { ... })`
3. Create `src/core/mock-data.ts/{folder}/pages/home.json` — folder = tenant id, or "resort" for resort-example
4. Create `src/core/mock-data.ts/{folder}/navigation.json` — header/footer nav
5. Add tenant import to `src/core/init.ts` so blocks are registered at startup
6. Add npm scripts: `dev:{short}`, `build:{short}`, `build:{short}:analyze` in package.json

## Tenant Config Shape

```typescript
export const config: TenantConfig = {
  id: "my-tenant",
  name: "My Site",
  domains: ["my-site.localhost", "my-site.com"],
  defaultLocale: "en",
  adapter: "mock",
  theme: {
    "color-primary": "#...",
    "color-background": "#...",
    "color-foreground": "#...",
    // ...
  },
};
```

## Testing

Run with: `npm run dev:resort` or `npm run dev:bike` (or add `dev:{short}` for new tenant)
